{
  "stem": "13469.3",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I should imagine it was taken over by Dutch people, or by the Nazis, or whatever kind of thing, and closed down.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So he didn't work there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I'm not sure that he did any kind of work.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But he was later on taken on by the Judenrat, which was the Jewish council.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Now, this was something that comes throughout the story.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The Germans were very clever in administering all these racial laws.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They obviously had the experience in Germany of how to do it.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And, basically, they got the Jews to administer all the laws themselves.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "The Germans would say what the laws were, and then the Jews had to make sure that they were carried out.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And anybody who trespassed kind of thing, first of all, was dealt with by the Jews.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And this is where the beginnings of the friction occurred, because in many places, the German Jews got themselves into the best positions kind of thing.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Not necessarily Amsterdam, but later on, in Westerbork, it was like that.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So in Amsterdam, the Germans set up the Judenrat.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And in fact, there was two Dutchman, a man called, Asha, who I think, believe, was a diamond man with loads of money, and a man called Cohen, who I think was a professor or something like that.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were in charge of the Judenrat, the Jewish administration in Amsterdam.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they got themselves a team of people to help them.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And this team grew, and grew, and grew.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And apparently, I found out eventually, there were two-and-a-half-thousand people, Jews, working for this Judenrat, administering all the various rules and regulations.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And my father, I found out, also worked for the Judenrat.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the big benefit of that, of working for the Judenrat, was that you were exempt from deportation.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
